ile:Med 3.png|15px]] 3rd place, ([[1996 UEFA Futsal Championship|1996]])\n| AMF World cup apps = 5\n| AMF World cup first = 1997\n| AMF World cup best = 4th place, ([[2015 AMF Futsal Men's World Cup|2015]])\n| Grand Prix apps    = 3\n| Grand Prix first   = [[2007 Grand Prix de Futsal|2007]]\n| Grand Prix best    = 5th place, ([[2007 Grand Prix de Futsal|2007]], [[2018 Grand Prix de Futsal|2018]])\n| Confederations cup apps = \n| Confederations cup first = \n| Confederations cup best = \n}}\nThe '''Belgium national futsal team''' is the national [[futsal]] team of [[Belgium]] and is controlled by the [[Belgian Football Association]] and represents the country in international [[futsal]] competitions, such as the [[FIFA Futsal World Cup]] and the [[UEFA Futsal Championship|European Championships]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://futsalfeed.com/original-content/belgium-futsal-story-hope-for-better-future|title=Belgium futsal story: Hope for better future|publisher=futsallfeed.com| accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>.\n\n==Tournament records==\n===FIFA Futsal World Cup===\n{{see also|FIFA Futsal World Cup}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=8|[[FIFA Futsal World Cup|FIFA World Cup Record]]\n|-\n!width=125|Year\n!width=150|Round\n\n!width=35|Pld\n!width=35|W\n!width=35|D\n!width=35|L\n!width=35|GS\n!width=35|GA\n|-bgcolor=#9acdff\n|[[1989 FIFA Futsal World Championship|Netherlands 1989]]||'''4th Place'''||8||5||2||1||22||11\n|-\n|[[1992 FIFA Futsal World Championship|Hong Kong 1992]]||Second Round||6||3||0||3||17||18\n|-\n|[[1996 FIFA Futsal World Championship|Spain 1996]]||Second Round||6||2||0||4||17||22\n|-\n|[[2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship|Guatemala 2000]]||''Did not qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|[[2004 FIFA Futsal World Championship|Chinese Taipei 2004]]||''Did not qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|[[2008 FIFA Futsal World Cup|Brazil 2008]]||''Did not qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|[[2012 FIFA Futsal World Cup|Thaila